---
title: Drop AFK
hidden: false
---
The **Drop AFK** glitch allows a player to enter a boss arena with a desired angle without triggering the **Boss AI**, leaving the boss idle. It is also a powerful tool for performing **skips** by allowing the player to clip **out of bounds**.

Performing this glitch requires **frame-perfect inputs**, it is preferably done on a **keyboard**, though it remains possible on console and controller.

- **AI Initialization**: For certain bosses, you must trigger their AI at least once (by entering the arena normally and then dying or quitting out) before the **Drop AFK** will work effectively.
- **Compatibility**: This glitch does not work on every boss. Some fog gates have geometry that is not compatible with the clip.
- **Invulnerability**: In some cases, a boss will not take damage if their AI is not activated. For example, **Kalameet** will remain invulnerable to damage if you bypass his trigger using this method.

## **How to Perform the Drop AFK**

1. **Setup**: You must have two separate keys or buttons bound to the "Action" command.
1. **Positioning**: Drop an item in front of the fog gate.
1. **Alignment**: Find the specific angle that aligns your character's feet with your objective. By using DSR Gadget you can take a look to your angle.
1. **Execution**: Press your first Action button, followed exactly **one frame later** by your second Action button.

This glitch requires a lot of practice to master the timing and positioning.

